<div style="margin:0 0 10px 0;">
                                          <div class="title darkNeutral">
                                            API Reference (2011-08-13)                                          </div>
                                          <div style="padding:10px;">
                                                                                                                                        
                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer463'));">
                                                      Countries                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer463" style="padding:5px; display:none;">
                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for country information:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=c</pre></div><br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br>At least one of the following is required:<br><br>To retrieve an individual country:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;iso=[COUNTRY_ISO]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve multiple countries:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;isos=[COUNTRY_ISO],[COUNTRY_ISO],...</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve all countries:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;iso=all
or
&amp;isos=all</pre></div><br><br>If any country is not found, no information will be returned for that country, not even an empty country element.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;country iso="EN"&gt;
  &lt;iso&gt;EN&lt;/iso&gt;
  &lt;name&gt;England&lt;/name&gt;
  &lt;time_offset&gt;-12&lt;/time_offset&gt;
  &lt;timezone&gt;Europe%2FLondon&lt;/timezone&gt;
&lt;/country&gt;</pre></div><br><br><b>Notes:</b><br><br><b>Time offset</b> The offset from Blackout Rugby Time in hours.<br><br><b>Timezone</b> The PHP timezone identifier.<br><br><b>Available country ISOs:</b><br><br><b>AR</b> Argentina<br><b>AU</b> Australia<br><b>BE</b> Belgium<br><b>BR</b> Brazil<br><b>CA</b> Canada<br><b>CL</b> Chile<br><b>HR</b> Croatia<br><b>CZ</b> Czech Republic<br><b>EN</b> England<br><b>FR</b> France<br><b>GE</b> Georgia<br><b>DE</b> Germany<br><b>HK</b> Hong Kong<br><b>IE</b> Ireland<br><b>IT</b> Italy<br><b>CI</b> Ivory Coast<br><b>JP</b> Japan<br><b>KE</b> Kenya<br><b>NA</b> Namibia<br><b>NL</b> Netherlands<br><b>NZ</b> New Zealand<br><b>PI</b> Pacific Islands<br><b>PL</b> Poland<br><b>PT</b> Portugal<br><b>RO</b> Romania<br><b>RU</b> Russia<br><b>SL</b> Scotland<br><b>ZA</b> South Africa<br><b>KR</b> South Korea<br><b>ES</b> Spain<br><b>US</b> United States<br><b>UY</b> Uruguay<br><b>WA</b> Wales<br><b>ZW</b> Zimbabwe</div>                                                  </div>
                                                </div>
                                                                                            
                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer459'));">
                                                      Date and Time                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer459" style="padding:5px; display:none;">
                                                    <div>In every response from the API, the main parent element contains information about the current date and time in Blackout Rugby. For example:<br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;blackoutrugby_api_response
  brt_timestamp="1265365926" 
  brt_sql="2010-02-05 22:32:06" 
  brt_iso_8601="2010-02-05T22:32:06+12:00" 
  season="7" round="16" day="5"&gt;
  ...
&lt;/blackoutrugby_api_response&gt;</pre></div><br><br>All times are calculated under a default timezone of <b>GMT+12</b>, which is equal to BRT (Blackout Rugby Time).<br><br>The first three attributes: brt_timestamp, brt_sql, and brt_iso_8601 hold the current BRT.<br><br><b>brt_timestamp</b> is a Unix timestamp.<br><b>brt_sql</b> is an SQL formatted datetime string.<br><b>brt_iso_8601</b> is the ISO 8601 formatted datetime string.<br><br>The last three attributes are fairly self explanatory, providing the current <b>season</b>, <b>round</b>, and <b>day</b> in Blackout Rugby.</div>                                                  </div>
                                                </div>
                                                                                            
                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer466'));">
                                                      Divisions                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer466" style="padding:5px; display:none;">
                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for division information:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=d</pre></div><br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br>At least one of the following is required:<br><br>To retrieve an individual division:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;divisionid=[DIVISION_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve multiple divisions:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;divisionids=[DIVISION_ID],[DIVISION_ID],...</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve a divisionid based on the season, country, and division:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;season=[SEASON]&amp;country_iso=[COUNTRY_ISO]&amp;division=[DIVISION]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve all divisions in a country:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;country_iso=[COUNTRY_ISO]</pre></div><br>This returns divisions for the current season.<br><br>Optionally you can specify the season as well:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;country_iso=[COUNTRY_ISO]&amp;season=[SEASON]</pre></div><br><br>If any division is not found, no information will be returned for that fixture, not even an empty division element.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;division id="926"&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;926&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;country_iso&gt;CA&lt;/country_iso&gt;
  &lt;season&gt;8&lt;/season&gt;
  &lt;division&gt;1&lt;/division&gt;
&lt;/division&gt;</pre></div></div>                                                  </div>
                                                </div>
                                                                                            
                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer481'));">
                                                      Finances                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer481" style="padding:5px; display:none;">
                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for financial information:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=fi</pre></div><br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;season=[SEASON]&amp;round=[ROUND]</pre></div><br>There is no need to provide a team id. Financial information will be provided only if a member key is provided, for the member's club.<br><br>If no financial information is available, no information will be returned, not even an empty element.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;transaction id="31991596"&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;31991596&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;teamid&gt;2&lt;/teamid&gt;
  &lt;amount&gt;5625&lt;/amount&gt;
  &lt;category&gt;Wages&lt;/category&gt;
  &lt;detail&gt;Youth Manager Wages&lt;/detail&gt;
  &lt;type&gt;2&lt;/type&gt;
  &lt;balance&gt;6446416&lt;/balance&gt;
  &lt;date&gt;1279540890&lt;/date&gt;
&lt;/transaction&gt;
&lt;transaction id="31991594"&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;31991594&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;teamid&gt;2&lt;/teamid&gt;
  &lt;amount&gt;12500&lt;/amount&gt;
  &lt;category&gt;Wages&lt;/category&gt;
  &lt;detail&gt;Youth Scout Wages&lt;/detail&gt;
  &lt;type&gt;2&lt;/type&gt;
  &lt;balance&gt;6452041&lt;/balance&gt;
  &lt;date&gt;1279540890&lt;/date&gt;
&lt;/transaction&gt;
...</pre></div><br><br><b>Notes:</b><br><br><b>Date</b> (Timestamp BRT) - The date of the transaction.<br><br><b>Type</b> - 1 = Income, 2 = Expense<br><br><b>Balance</b> - The bank balance after the transaction.<br><br><b>Sorting</b> - By default, transactions are sorted by Category. If you want them in order of processing, you will need to sort by ID locally.</div>                                                  </div>
                                                </div>
                                                                                            
                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer465'));">
                                                      Fixtures                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer465" style="padding:5px; display:none;">
                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for fixture information:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=f</pre></div><br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br>At least one of the following is required:<br><br>To retrieve an individual fixture:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;fixtureid=[FIXTURE_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve a group of fixtures:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;fixtureids=[FIXTURE_ID],[FIXTURE_ID],...</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve the last X fixtures for a team:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;teamid=[TEAM_ID]&amp;last=[NUMBER_OF_FIXTURES]

optionally, you can filter these fixtures by competition:

&amp;teamid=[TEAM_ID]&amp;last=[NUMBER_OF_FIXTURES]&amp;competition=[COMPETITION]
</pre></div><br>See notes for valid competitions.<br><br><br>To retrieve all future fixtures for a team:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;future=[TEAM_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve all past fixtures for a team:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;past=[TEAM_ID]</pre></div><br>WARNING: Please use this request sparingly, as it can return hundreds of fixtures.<br><br>To get youth fixtures, add the youth flag:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">...&amp;youth=1</pre></div><br><br>To get National fixtures, add the National flag:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">...&amp;nat=1</pre></div><br><br>To get Under 20 fixtures, add the Under 20 flag:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">...&amp;u20=1</pre></div><br><br><b>For club fixtures only:</b><br><br>To retrieve fixtures from the last league round:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;latest=[LEAGUE_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve fixtures from a specific league round:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;leagueid=[LEAGUE_ID]&amp;season=[SEASON]&amp;round=[ROUND]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve all fixtures in a league ordered by round:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;leagueid=[LEAGUE_ID]</pre></div><br><br><b>For National\U20 fixtures only:</b><br><br>To retrieve fixtures from the last round:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;latest=1&amp;nat=1
or
&amp;latest=1&amp;u20=1</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve all round robin fixtures for the current season ordered by round:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;roundrobin=1&amp;nat=1
or
&amp;roundrobin=1&amp;u20=1</pre></div><br><br><b>3rd Party Friendly Competitions</b><br><br>To retrieve fixtures for any given round for a 3rd party competition:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;friendlycompid=[FRIENDLY_COMP_ID]
or
&amp;friendlycompid=[FRIENDLY_COMP_ID]&amp;season=[SEASON[&amp;round=[ROUND]</pre></div><br>If a season/round is not specified, the current round is used.<br>The ID for a 3rd party competition can be found in the URL on the competition control panel summary page.<br><br>If any fixture is not found, no information will be returned for that fixture, not even an empty fixture element.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;fixture id="3812580"&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;3812580&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;season&gt;8&lt;/season&gt;
  &lt;country_iso&gt;NZ&lt;/country_iso&gt;
  &lt;leagueid&gt;61808&lt;/leagueid&gt;
  &lt;round&gt;2&lt;/round&gt;
  &lt;hometeamid&gt;21064&lt;/hometeamid&gt;
  &lt;guestteamid&gt;2&lt;/guestteamid&gt;
  &lt;competition&gt;League&lt;/competition&gt;
  &lt;botmatch&gt;0&lt;/botmatch&gt;
  &lt;matchstart&gt;1266633300&lt;/matchstart&gt;
&lt;/fixture&gt;</pre></div><br><br><b>Notes:</b><br><br><b>Match start</b> (Timestamp BRT) - The date in Blackout Rugby Time when the match starts, or started.<br><br><b>Bot match</b> If this value is 1, the match was played between two bots, and a full match did not take place. So you cannot request match reports for botmatches for example.<br><br><b>Valid competitions</b><br><b>Seniors:</b> Friendly, ThursdayFriendly, Cup, League, SemiFinal, BronzeFinal, Final, Qualifier<br><b>Juniors:</b> League<br><b>National:</b> International, WorldCup<br><b>Under 20:</b> U20International, U20WorldCup</div>                                                  </div>
                                                </div>
                                                                                            
                                                <div>
