                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for fixture based statistics:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=fs</pre></div><br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br>At least one of the following is required:<br><br>To retrieve an individual fixture's statistics:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;fixtureid=[FIXTURE_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve a group of fixture's statistics:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;fixtureids=[FIXTURE_ID],[FIXTURE_ID],...</pre></div><br><br><b>WARNING:</b> The above queries alone will return all team statistics and all player statistics available for a match. Please use these sparingly as they return a lot of data. Where possible, use one of the following limiters:<br><br>To only retrieve team statistics for a specified team:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;fixtureid=[FIXTURE_ID]&amp;teamstats=[TEAM_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To only retrieve players statistics for a specified team:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;fixtureid=[FIXTURE_ID]&amp;teamplayersstats=[TEAM_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To only retrieve players statistics for a specified player:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;fixtureid=[FIXTURE_ID]&amp;playerstats=[PLAYER_ID]</pre></div><br><br>If any fixtures are not found, no information will be returned for that fixture, not even an empty element. If any team or player statistics for a fixture are not found, I.E. if a correct fixture ID is provided, but an incorrect team ID is provided, empty elements may be returned.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;fixture_statistics id="3812596"&gt;
