                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer476'));">
                                                      Rankings                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer476" style="padding:5px; display:none;">
                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for rankings information:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=rk</pre></div><br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br><br>To retrieve world rankings for clubs:<br>World rankings are the default, and will be returned if you don't specify a country, region, or league.<br><br>To retrieve rankings for a specific country:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;iso=[COUNTRY_ISO]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve rankings for a specific region:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;regionid=[REGION_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve rankings for a specific league:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;leagueid=[LEAGUE_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve International rankings:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;nat=1</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve Under 20 rankings:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;u20=1</pre></div><br><br>By default, for all requests mentioned above, a maximum of 100 rankings will be returned at a time, starting at index 0 for the first ranking. If you want to specify a new start value, i.e. to get the next 100 rankings, you would append:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;start=100</pre></div><br><br>If you don't need 100 rankings, you can set this as a lower value, for example, to request only the top 20 rankings, you can use:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;limit=20</pre></div><br><br>If any rankings are not found, no information will be returned for that ranking, not even an empty element.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;team id="1977"&gt;
  &lt;ranking&gt;1&lt;/ranking&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;1977&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;name&gt;Magratheans&lt;/name&gt;
  &lt;country_iso&gt;NZ&lt;/country_iso&gt;
  &lt;points&gt;87.5096&lt;/points&gt;
&lt;/team&gt;</pre></div></div>                                                  </div>
                                                </div>
                                                                                            
                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer464'));">
                                                      Regions                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer464" style="padding:5px; display:none;">
                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for region information:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=r</pre></div><br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br>At least one of the following is required:<br><br>To retrieve an individual region:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;regionid=[REGION_ID]</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve multiple regions:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;regionids=[REGION_ID],[REGION_ID],...</pre></div><br><br>To retrieve all regions in a country:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;country=[COUNTRY_ISO]</pre></div><br><br>If any region is not found, no information will be returned for that region, not even an empty region element.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;region id="1"&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;1&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;name&gt;Auckland&lt;/name&gt;
  &lt;country_iso&gt;NZ&lt;/country_iso&gt;
&lt;/region&gt;</pre></div></div>                                                  </div>
                                                </div>
                                                                                            
                                                <div>
                                                  <div>
