                                                    <a href="javascript: expand(document.getElementById('answer482'));">
                                                      Transfer Market                                                    </a>
                                                  </div>
                                                  <div id="answer482" style="padding: 5px; display: block;">
                                                    <div><b>Request</b><br>To tell the API that this is a request for transfer market information:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;r=tm</pre></div><br><br>By default, all auctions are returned, sorted by nearest deadline first.<br><br><b>Additional Request Data</b><br>All of the following requests are optional.<br><br>To request a specific sort type:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;sortby=[SORT_BY]</pre></div><br>[SORT_BY] can be any of: "name", "price", "deadline", "nationality", "age", or "ranking".<br><br>To request a specific sort order:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;sortorder=[SORT_ORDER]</pre></div><br>[SORT_ORDER] can be either: "asc", or "desc".<br><br>To offset your results:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;offset=[OFFSET]</pre></div><br>For example, an offset of 0, will start your results at the first auction in the result set. And an offset of 10 will start your results at the 11th auction.<br><br>To limit your results:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;limit=[LIMIT]</pre></div><br>For example, a limit of 10, will return a maximum of 10 results.<br><br>The offset and limit can, and should be used where possible to reduce the amount of auctions returned at once. For example, &amp;offset=0&amp;limit=10 would return the first 10 auctions, and &amp;offset=10&amp;limit=10 would return auctions 11-20.<br><br>To get players from a certain team:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;teamid=[TEAMID]</pre></div><br>NOTE: You cannot use any search parameters when getting players from a given team.<br><br><b>Searching</b><br><br>Any and all of the following search criteria can be given:<br><br>To search by price:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;priceMin=[PRICE_INTEGER]
and/or
&amp;priceMax=[PRICE_INTEGER]</pre></div><br><br>To search by age:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;ageMin=[AGE_INTEGER]
and/or
&amp;ageMax=[AGE_INTEGER]</pre></div><br><br>To search by CSR:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;csrMin=[CSR_INTEGER]
and/or
&amp;csrMax=[CSR_INTEGER]</pre></div><br><br>To search by Nationality:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;nationality=[COUNTRY_ISO]</pre></div><br><br>To search by player attribute:<br><br>First, you must specify an attribute:<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;skill[X]=[ATTRIBUTE]</pre></div><br>[X] Must be an integer. It can be any integer, e.g. &amp;skill1=<br><br>[ATTRIBUTE] can be any of the following: "stamina", "handling", "defense", "attack", "technique", "strength", "jumping", "speed", "agility", "kicking", "form", "height", "weight", "salary", "discipline", "aggression", "leadership", or "experience".<br><br>As well as the specified attribute, you must specify either a minimum, or a  maximum, or both.<br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&amp;skill[X]min=[MIN_INTEGER]
and/or
&amp;skill[X]max=[MAX_INTEGER]</pre></div><br>[X] Must be the same integer as used for setting the attribute. E.g. &amp;skill1=stamina&amp;skill1min=10<br><br>For any attribute with a skill level, you should use the integer level, I.E. Non-existant = 1, Despicable = 2, Horrible = 3, etc.<br><br>For height, weight, and salary, you should use the applicable integer.<br><br>If any there are no auctions, no information will be returned.<br><br><b>Response</b><br><br><div class="code"><pre style="margin:0; padding:0;">&lt;auction id="237556"&gt;
